commend using Tranquil during pregnancy or while breastfeeding without consulting your healthcare provider.<\/p>"}},"text_FLb344":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"Does Tranquil contain melatonin?","text":"<p>No, Tranquil is completely melatonin-free. It supports your body’s natural ability to relax and improve sleep quality, without disrupting your natural rhythm.<\/p>"}},"text_EKYJgt":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"What makes Tranquil different from other sleep supplements?","text":"<p>Tranquil focuses on improving sleep quality naturally, without melatonin, by supporting relaxation, reducing stress, and helping your body maintain a healthy sleep cycle.<\/p>"}},"text_JXpzG7":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"Will I feel groggy in the morning?","text":"<p>No, Tranquil is designed to support deep, restorative sleep so you wake up feeling clear, refreshed, and ready for the day.<\/p>"}},"text_PnTKBC":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"When should I take Tranquil?","text":"<p>For best results, take it in the evening, around 30–60 minutes before bedtime as part of your wind-down routine.<\/p>"}},"text_CDjCWe":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"Can I take Tranquil every night?","text":"<p>Yes, Tranquil is designed for daily use and works best when taken consistently as part of your evening routine.<\/p>"}},"text_DQpD7N":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"Is Tranquil suitable for long-term use?","text":"<p>Yes, the formula is designed to support your sleep over time, helping you build a more consistent and balanced sleep pattern.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["text_43mDRh","text_bNJYGn","text_eGY6Gw","text_Tx9cFt","text_FLb344","text_EKYJgt","text_JXpzG7","text_PnTKBC","text_CDjCWe","text_DQpD7N"],"settings":{"layout":"one-column","show_accordion_divider":false,"title":"Frequently Asked Questions - Sleep","subheading":"","text":"","tabs_bg_color":"#fafafa","bg_color_secondary":false,"text_color":"text-dark","width":"wrapper--narrow","padding_top":60,"padding_bottom